# Autoclosure

Use this when work already exists in the tree and the user asks whether
anything is missing, to clean it up, or to close it safely.

## Flow

1. Read latest user request, `VISION.md`, and any named plan/spec.
2. Inspect the current diff/status without reverting unrelated work.
3. Classify touched surfaces: gameplay, UI/HUD, Three.js/canvas, docs/plans,
   tests, agent workflow, config, assets.
4. Run the relevant checks or record N/A:
   - `npm run build`;
   - focused Playwright/tests;
   - browser/canvas proof;
   - source-backed docs audit;
   - `npx skiller@latest apply` plus mirror audit for agent changes.
5. Run `autoreview` or an equivalent self-review for non-trivial diffs.
6. Fix accepted P0/P1 and acceptance-breaking issues. Convert lower-priority
   cleanup into explicit follow-up notes unless the user asked for polish.
7. Update `VISION.md` if the closure reveals reusable doctrine.

## Stop

Stop when the current requested work is cohesive, verified, and any remaining
risk is explicit. Do not keep polishing indefinitely.
